cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This is the most likely category as the paper is focused on using SAT solvers for cryptanalysis of cryptographic functions. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - This category is likely as the paper describes the use of volunteer computing for solving hard instances of the Boolean satisfiability problem. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - This category is likely as the paper describes the use of discrete optimization algorithms for partitioning the original problem into subproblems. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - This category is possible as the paper may describe the implementation of the SAT@home project and the programming languages used. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - This category is possible as the paper may describe the system architecture and control mechanisms used in the SAT@home project.
